# Development Workflow

## Getting Started
1. Install dependencies: `npm install`
2. Copy environment variables: `cp env.example .env.local`
3. Set up API keys for Mapbox and Unsplash
4. Run development server: `npm run dev`

## Development Commands
- `npm run dev` - Start development server
- `npm run build` - Build for production
- `npm run start` - Start production server
- `npm run lint` - Run ESLint

## File Structure Guidelines
- Add new pages in [src/app/](mdc:src/app/) directory
- Create components in [src/components/](mdc:src/components/)
- Add utilities in [src/lib/](mdc:src/lib/)
- Create custom hooks in [src/hooks/](mdc:src/hooks/)

## Component Development
- Use existing components as templates
- Follow the established patterns
- Use proper TypeScript interfaces
- Implement proper error handling

## Testing
- Test components in isolation
- Test responsive behavior
- Test API integrations
- Test accessibility features

## Deployment
- Build the project with `npm run build`
- Set environment variables in deployment platform
- Use Vercel for optimal Next.js deployment
- Ensure all API keys are properly configured